track_notes:
Most of this hike is along an abandoned hiking trail.  This made progress even more difficult than most bushwhacks.  

There is hope that the trail can be adopted and maintained in the future.

The trail has been cleared so this summit is smooth sailing all the way.  I recommend following this track and starting the off-trail hike sooner rather than later.  The slope is more gentle that way and is open forest.

2.6 mile hike with 1350 EG.  The Oakey Mtn Loop Trail goes all the way to the gap east of Oakey Mtn making for a more gentle off-trail climb to the summit.  Be cautious around 34.9451, -83.3492 as the trail makes a hard right turn, but a good trail (but unmarked) continues straight ahead.  There is a circular white trail marker on a tree to your left heading up and that marks the right-hand turn.
track_title: Oakey Mtn via trail to ridgeline
